summary: An automated email from E2 travel services notifying a traveler that their voucher for a trip to Santa Monica from September 17-20, 2019 is late. The trip's purpose is listed as 'R19NYS13842 - U.S. v. Epstein - Witness Interviews', indicating it was for Department of Justice personnel conducting interviews related to the Epstein case.

events.title: Witness Interview Trip Authorization
events.description: A trip to Santa Monica was authorized for the purpose of conducting witness interviews for the case 'U.S. v. Epstein'.

events.title: End of Witness Interview Trip
events.description: The authorized trip for Epstein case witness interviews in Santa Monica concluded.

keyFacts: The document is a travel voucher reminder email from the DOJ's E2 travel system.
The trip's purpose was explicitly for 'U.S. v. Epstein - Witness Interviews'.
The trip occurred from September 17 to September 20, 2019, to Santa Monica.
The document reference 'R19NYS13842' is likely a case or docket number for the Epstein prosecution.
The email indicates ongoing investigative activity (witness interviews) by the DOJ in the Epstein case in late 2019.
